 aav - ANSI/ASCII Art Viewer
---------------------------------------------------------------------
aav is a tiny application which draws your favorite ANSI/ASCII pr0n
on your terminal. Actually, your terminal is able to draw it natively
since ANSI escape code is supported but most of those pr0n use the
code page 437 font as a charset. aav just convert that crappy
non-portable charset to unicode and try to draw it as best possible.

 Supported format
---------------------------------------------------------------------
. ASC / NFO / ANS / DIZ

 System required
---------------------------------------------------------------------
. Unix-like OS
. UTF8 locale
. UTF8 font compliant
 
 Compile
---------------------------------------------------------------------
gcc -o aav aav.c -std=c99

